    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-10T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-10T19:00:00-05:00" n="184"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/4722: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-10T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 10, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1191. With reference to Department’s number 1039, October 20. Large number
                    refugees in Sweden and Switzerland make it urgent <pb facs="0227" n="217"
                        xml:id="pg_217"/> to announce proposed joint declaration on repatriation in
                    near future. Other countries have not been informed of proposed declaration
                    pending Soviet Government’s acceptance. You are requested to discuss this with
                    Soviet authorities at earliest appropriate date and endeavor to secure their
                    acceptance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
